JOHANNESBURG - The annual Back to the City Hip Hop festival, a celebration of Freedom Day, took place on Thursday, 27 April, in Johannesburg.Rappers have a huge following, often championing youths' hopes and aspirations, and helping them stay informed about what's happing in the country. eNCA asked them what freedom really means to them.Cassper Nyovest said, "A lot of young people were born into freedom so they don't know how precious of a gift it is. Our parents are the ones who understand the difference between then and now we didn't really get to see it."In a generation that preaches that one should stay woke - a meme derived from the phrase stay awake - we can only hope their messages are well-received.*View the attached video for rappers thoughts on the meaning of freedom.eNCA